4. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper discusses the existence of quasi-regular sequences and their properties, which are related to data structures and algorithms. This makes cs.DS a possible sub-category. 
5. cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper discusses the use of ergodic theory to show the existence of deterministic quasi-regular sequences, which is related to information theory. This makes cs.IT a possible sub-category.
